node.text:
Today, we announce @nabrliving.

Co-founded by @bjarkeingels , Roni Bahar, and Nick Chim, Nabr is reimagining the future of urban living, providing scalable, consumer-first housing. Nabr will offer an end-to-end product, integrating everything from design and development, to the sales and management of the real estate process. Driven by the vision of Bjarke Ingels, Nabr takes a human-centric approach to design.

Nabr is set to optimize the real estate development process, providing high-quality homes that benefit both residents and communities. For more information, head to the link in our bio.

node.text: The global energy system needs to undergo its most profound change in centuries to realize a world run on renewable sources. The metals required for this green transition are taking a detrimental toll on the environment. To change that, BIG and The Metals Company have designed a fleet of robotic vessels to responsibly harvest metals from the abyssal seafloor, for the production of e-cars and batteries—one step in forming a sustainable circular metals economy for future generations.

node.text: A few months after the first passengers tested BIG's design for @VirginHyperloop’s #Pegasus pod, today the the end-to-end future #hyperloop experience is unveiled. The newly-released concept video takes the viewer step-by-step through a hyperloop journey, from arriving at the BIG-designed portal to boarding the pod. The collaborations include Teague for the pod designs, SeeThree for the video and animation, and @man_made_music for the score and sonic identity – to design a comprehensive, multi-sensory passenger experience that surpasses that of any other form of mass transit. Link in to article in bio.

node.text: #CapitaSpring, the newest 280-metre-tall #skyscraper in Singapore’s Central Business District, tops out! BIG & @crassociati's design for the 51-storey landmark in Raffles Place is set to make a distinctive mark on the #Singapore skyline with a Green Oasis: the building’s exterior façade consists of vertical elements that are pulled apart to allow glimpses into the oases blooming from the base, core and rooftop. A dynamic interplay of orthogonal lines and lush greenery presents itself in the contrasting textures of steel and glass, interweaved with tropical vegetation. @capitaland SING on big.dk

node.text: BIG teams up with @icon3dtech and @spacexarch, to work with @NASA on beginning research & development of a space-based construction system that could support future exploration of the #Moon. #NASA has signaled that, through the #Artemis program, the Moon will be the first off-Earth site for #sustainable surface exploration. BIG's design for ICON's #ProjectOlympus will be a sustainable #lunarhabitat, the first human foray into extra-terrestrial construction with robust structures that provide better thermal, radiation, and micrometeorite protection than metal or inflatable habitats can offer. From landing pads to habitats, these collective efforts together with NASA and SEArch+ are driven by the need to make humanity a spacefaring civilization. Read more on @FastCompany – link in bio!

Last week, we unveiled AI CITY—the new hi-tech campus dedicated to #TerminusGroup's ambitions in #artificialintelligence, #robotics, networking & big data. Located in #Chongqing, also known as the 'Mountain City' in southwest China, #AI_CITY is comprised of Cloud Valley, conceived as two plots that mimic each other's opposites: the Mountain, which forms a striking landmark and shelter to a protected network of courtyards for public functions, and the Valley, which offers the largest publicly accessible green rooftop in #China for open-air events. AI CITY is envisioned as a city where people, #technology and nature thrive together – with spaces designed for all types of life: human life, plant life, animal life & even #artificial life. @terminus_aicity @terminus_ai 
 
Take the tour on big.dk: https://big.dk/#projects-tfc

node.title: BIG unveils AI CITY for Terminus Group in Chongqing, China

node.text: BIG, @hijjas_architects_and_planners & @rambollgroup are selected as winners of Penang State Government's competition to design a masterplan for #Penang South Islands, providing Penangites with approximately 4.6km of public beaches, 600 acres of parks and a 25km waterfront! Our proposal – #BiodiverCity – supports the #Penang2030 vision with a clear focus on livability, on stimulating a socially and economically inclusive development, and on environmental #sustainability for future generations. BiodiverCity will be a new sustainable, global destination where #cultural, ecological and economic growth is secured and where people & nature co-exist in one of the most #biodiverse places on the planet at the southern shore of Penang Island. Take the tour on big.dk (link in bio)! Animation by BIG & @lucianracovitan

node.title: BiodiverCity Paves Sustainable Future for Penang Island

⠀

Today, we announce @nabrliving.

Co-founded by @bjarkeingels , Roni Bahar, and Nick Chim, Nabr is reimagining the future of urban living, providing scalable, consumer-first housing. Nabr will offer an end-to-end product, integrating everything from design and development, to the sales and management of the real estate process. Driven by the vision of Bjarke Ingels, Nabr takes a human-centric approach to design.

Nabr is set to optimize the real estate development process, providing high-quality homes that benefit both residents and communities. For more information, head to the link in our bio.

Together with @ICON3dtech and @NASA, BIG has today announced Mars Dune Alpha–a 3D-printed habitat, designed by BIG, that will aid in long-duration, exploration-class science missions. 

Giving form to the future of Mars habitation, Mars Dune Alpha’s analog missions – part of NASA’s CHAPEA program – will provide valuable insights for NASA’s space food system, as well as physical and behavioral health and performance outcomes for future space missions. The 1,700 square-foot structure, located at Johnson Space Center in Houston and 3D printed by ICON’s next-gen Vulcan construction system, will be home to the crew of which NASA is now actively seeking.

For more information, head to the link in bio.

Warped visions of Superkilen 🌀 ⠀
⠀
Superkilen is a half-mile long urban space in Copenhagen, wedged into one of the most ethnically diverse and socially-challenged neighborhoods in Denmark. Conceived as a giant exhibition of urban best practices, it comprises a collection of global found objects that come from 60 different home countries of the people inhabiting the adjacent area. ⠀
⠀
Here, Superkilen is captured in a surreal way, from a bird's eye view. ⠀
⠀
📷 John Kroll

The new @Suitsupply headquarters is receiving some #biophilia! Here, the trees are being raised to the roof gardens of Terrace Tower. ⠀
⠀
The building is a part of Kop Zuidas master-plan, located in the south of #Amsterdam. The design is based on a multifunctional hybrid of two office typologies: a generic office tower and a generic horizontal block.  The hybrid is articulated through a gradual setback in the front façade—liberating the front area of the building and creating a green pocket dedicated to the public realm—and a sequence of terraces in the back, providing breakout areas for employees to enjoy a daily dose of #nature. ⠀
⠀
📷 Marcel Steinbach

When a sailing club and a youth center were going to use the same building, our design team had to get creative. Children needed outdoor space to play, and the sailing club needed somewhere to moor their boats. The result: boat storage beneath an undulating public landscape with water on all sides, rising and falling like manmade waves 🌊

📷 Maritime Youth House, Paolo Rosselli

As highlighted by @Sleepermagazine's latest Top Hotel Projects NYC Report, the city that never sleeps is living up to its name, with a slew of new hotel developments in the pipeline. 

Included in the list is The XI, a 890,000-square-foot, mixed-use project composed of two twisting towers, designed by BIG. Housed in this pair of twisting towers will be a mix of residential and commercial spaces, including @Sixsenses' first North America-based hotel.

At the base, the two towers pull away from each other and the neighboring buildings to maximize urban space and views. As they rise, the towers morph and re-orient to take advantage of the best views at the upper levels, while also allowing for un-obstructed Hudson River views towards the west and city views towards the south, east, and northeast. 

📷 DBOX

We're dreaming of BIG's Aarhus Harbor Bath during this Danish heatwave! 💦 ⠀
⠀
The Aarhus Harbor Bath zig-zags gently into the island, extends all the way out into the harbor pool, and then back again. Swimmers can enjoy the circular diving pool, a children’s pool, the 50m long lap pool, or one of the two saunas that are tucked underneath the public boardwalk (which doubles as a viewing platform who those who prefer to stay dry). Whom do you want to bring? 🐬 ⠀
⠀
 📷  Rasmus Hjortshøj
